      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver must demonstrate correct implementation of governing equations through benchmark problems. Published benchmark results for internal flow acceptable at MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent code verification demonstrated through FDA benchmark nozzle and backward-facing step cases. Discretization schemes verified against analytical solutions for laminar pipe flow. Published ASME V&V 20 benchmark results cited. Requirement met."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence study required with at least three systematically refined meshes. GCI < 5% on primary QoI (NIH) acceptable at MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study performed: coarse (4.2M cells), medium (11.8M cells), fine (31.4M cells) with refinement ratio r = 1.41. Grid convergence index (GCI) for NIH: 2.1% (medium-fine pair). Apparent order of convergence p = 1.87, consistent with second-order scheme. Discretization error well-characterized; achieves Gradation 3 performance. Requirement exceeded."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions must be documented with sufficient detail to enable boundary condition specification. Operating flow rates and rotational speeds must be reported with measurement uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "FDA generic pump experimental data (Hariharan et al. 2011) provides fully documented test conditions: flow rates 2.5–7.5 L/min, rotational speeds 2000–3500 RPM, blood analog fluid properties (glycerol-water, viscosity 3.5 cP). Inlet/outlet boundary conditions specified from reported pressure-flow curves. Measurement uncertainties reported for all primary variables. Requirement met."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Predicted QoIs must be compared quantitatively against experimental data with documented error metrics. Agreement within experimental uncertainty acceptable at MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "NIH predictions compared against experimental measurements at five operating points. Mean absolute relative error 8.3%; root mean square error 0.0012 g/100L. All predictions within one standard deviation of experimental mean. Bland-Altman analysis confirms no systematic bias. Requirement met."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model QoIs (NIH, shear stress distribution) must be directly linked to the clinical decision outcome. Mechanistic justification for QoI selection required.",
      "rationale": "NIH is the regulatory-accepted metric for pump hemolysis assessment (FDA guidance 2010). Shear stress distribution directly drives the power-law hemolysis damage model (Giersiepen et al. 1990). Both QoIs mechanistically linked to erythrocyte lysis under sub-lethal shear exposure. Relative hemolysis index (RH) derived from NIH enables direct comparison against predicate device. Requirement met."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments must use the same pump geometry or a documented surrogate with justified similarity. Blood analog fluid must replicate relevant rheological properties.",
      "rationale": "Validation performed on the identical FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry used in the COU. Blood analog (glycerol-water, 3.5 cP) replicates Newtonian viscosity of blood at high shear rates relevant to pump operation (>100 s⁻¹). Operating conditions span the clinical CPB range (2.5–6.0 L/min, 2000–3500 RPM). Validation domain encompasses COU operating space. Requirement met."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence and round-off error characterization. At MRL 2 with commercial solver, documented residual convergence criteria acceptable without explicit round-off quantification.",
      "rationale": "Residual convergence to 1×10⁻⁵ for all equations documented. Double-precision arithmetic used throughout. Explicit round-off error quantification not required at MRL 2 for this factor. Factor not assessed beyond residual monitoring; acceptable per MRL 2 requirements."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Documentation of analyst qualifications and review process. At MRL 2, peer review of simulation setup sufficient.",
      "rationale": "CFD analyses performed by analyst with 8 years rotodynamic pump simulation experience. Setup reviewed by independent senior analyst. Formal use-error quantification not required at MRL 2. Factor scoped to documentation review only."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Justification of turbulence model and hemolysis damage model selection. At MRL 2, literature-based justification acceptable without formal model-form uncertainty quantification.",
      "rationale": "k-ω SST turbulence model selected based on published performance for rotating internal flows (Menter 1994). Giersiepen power-law hemolysis model selected per FDA guidance and literature consensus. Model form uncertainty not formally quantified at MRL 2; literature justification provided. Factor not assessed beyond model selection rationale."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Documentation of input parameter sources and nominal values. At MRL 2, traceable input specification without formal input uncertainty propagation acceptable.",
      "rationale": "All model inputs (fluid properties, boundary conditions, geometric parameters) documented with sources. Blood analog properties from manufacturer specifications; boundary conditions from experimental records. Formal input uncertainty propagation not required at MRL 2 for this factor. Traceability established."
